<!channel>
Happy Demo Day everyone!

There is no lecture or reason to log into the main class Zoom tonight. Demos will begin right at 5:30. Here's some info you'll need to be successful tonight:

1. Review this <https://docs.google.com/document/d/1I6TRMfjSp6il4rPeJ1IudoINAh9PS2HpfKdJupdVLk0/edit?usp=sharing|Project Demo Learner Guide>. This will show how you will be assessed. Like interviews, you must score a 3 in all sections to graduate, 4 for apprenticeship program.
2. Just like for Project Checkpoints, you will be meeting with a TA for a different project group who will Slack you a link. 
3. When not in your demo, you should be working on your Ready for Placement Survey (due today), Professional Development Plan (due Monday), and your resume edits.
4. For your demo, you will be asked a series of questions under each of the three categories: Project Overview, Technical, and Professional. You'll also do a code walkthrough of your specific features, and each of your 3 features must be complete and working at the time of demo. *You will be required to share your screen while completing the code walkthrough. Please have your project open before the demo begins to make sure that you are ready to go for the code walkthrough.* 
5. Your slide decks are to be submitted in your Ready for Placement survey, not used as a part of your demo.
6. Scores for demos will go up on Canvas early next week, and makeup instructions will also go out for those requiring makeups by Monday's class time. As general advice, if you feel your demo did not go well, be ready to go again Monday during class.
Regarding makeups and deadlines:

1. The front page of this Project Demo document outlines a) items needed for graduation, b) items needed for apprenticeship, and c) what to expect when the class ends. *Please review carefully as those items are not negotiable.*
2. Some of you will be contacted by Colin tonight to conduct a makeup interview in addition to your demo. He is sending a message to those individuals now, so if you do not hear from him by the 5pm, you will not have an interview tonight. 
3. Other folks requiring a makeup interview for graduation or apprenticeship will receive additional scheduling information tomorrow. We have some wonderful volunteers assisting, and I am currently collecting their availability. Please check your Slack tomorrow afternoon for this information.
4. The deadline to raise scores/have approvals met to graduate from this course is February 21. You'll notice this is after your Graduation Date of February 5. This gives you all (and staff) more breathing room for makeups. My strong recommendation is still to be as proactive as possible on your end with preparing for interviews and making edits to your resume as requested, as staff balances all 150 of you and other classes. If you have not met all requirements by February 5, you will still be honored at graduation, but will not receive a digital certificate until all requirements are met. 
5. The deadline to raise scores/have approvals met for the apprenticeship program is March 6. This is 30 days post graduation. Again, please be as proactive as possible with preparing for interviews and making edits to your resume as requested to ensure you meet this deadline. 
6. Next week we will use class time for makeup demos and interviews. You will receive notice Monday before class starts if you are conducting a makeup demo or interview that night. We are still working on a plan for makeup demos after next Thursday if that becomes necessary. 
7. Feedback for folks who passed their first interview will go out eventually, but staff is currently prioritizing getting folks graduation- and apprenticeship-ready.
I know this is a lot of information. I will also post the info about makeups and deadlines this as a page in Canvas. Feel free to respond to this post with questions you may have.
